                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d779">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Eddy</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">St. Petersburg</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1904-12-16">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 16, 1904</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Mr. Eddy reports that the captains of the <hi rend="italic">Calchas</hi> and <hi
                        rend="italic">Knight Commander</hi> have entered appeals en bloc, covering
                    American goods, and that the cases will be heard in January.)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
